        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 10:29PM CDT by NWS Bismarck ND</headline>
        <description>At 1028 PM CDT/928 PM MDT/, Doppler radar was tracking a strong
thunderstorm 17 miles south of Carson, or 33 miles northeast of
Lemmon, moving southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Standing Rock.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
